        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(gateway): preserve indentation when recombining non-streaming replies",
        "body": "AI-assisted: yes (OpenClaw agent-authored).\nTesting: targeted local validation (gateway regression tests + targeted lint + pre-commit repo checks).\n\n## Summary\n\n- Companion to merged #55960, not a duplicate: #55960 fixed indentation loss while stripping inline reply directives in `src/utils/directive-tags.ts`; this PR fixes the remaining gateway-layer loss when non-streaming reply parts are recombined in `src/gateway/server-methods/chat.ts`.\n- Preserve each non-streaming payload chunk as authored when recombining it, so indentation-sensitive content survives payload boundaries.\n- Reuse that same combiner for `/btw` side results so sibling non-streaming gateway paths behave consistently.\n- Normalize `CRLF` / `CR` / `LF` boundary trimming and add focused regression coverage for the single-newline, `/btw`, and CRLF cases.\n- Scope boundary: no streaming-path formatting changes, no Markdown parsing changes, and no channel-specific formatting rules.\n\n## Change Type (select all)\n\n- [x] Bug fix\n- [ ] Feature\n- [ ] Refactor\n- [ ] Docs\n- [ ] Security hardening\n- [ ] Chore/infra\n\n## Scope (select all touched areas)\n\n- [x] Gateway / orchestration\n- [ ] Skills / tool execution\n- [ ] Auth / tokens\n- [ ] Memory / storage\n- [ ] Integrations\n- [ ] API / contracts\n- [ ] UI / DX\n- [ ] CI/CD / infra\n\n## Linked Issue/PR\n\n- Closes #42576\n- Related #29377\n- Companion to merged #55960\n\n## Relationship to #55960\n\nMerged PR #55960 fixed one real whitespace-loss layer: inline reply-directive stripping in the shared parser (`src/utils/directive-tags.ts`).\n\nThis PR fixes a separate remaining layer later in the pipeline: gateway non-streaming recombination of final reply chunks (and `/btw` side-result chunks) in `src/gateway/server-methods/chat.ts`.\n\nSo the two PRs are adjacent and complementary, not overlapping duplicates.\n\n## User-visible / Behavior Changes\n\nNon-streaming final replies and `/btw` side results now preserve indentation when formatted content spans multiple payloads. When one chunk already ends with a single newline and the next chunk does not start with one, the gateway now preserves that authored single newline instead of forcing a blank line. The combiner also trims `CRLF` / `CR` / `LF` cleanly at outer boundaries so Windows-style line endings do not leak stray carriage returns.\n\nThis fixes the flattened-output symptom reported against Matrix, but the bug itself is generic to gateway non-streaming recombination of indentation-sensitive content rather than Matrix-specific formatting.\n\n## Security Impact (required)\n\n- New permissions/capabilities? (`Yes/No`) No\n- Secrets/tokens handling changed? (`Yes/No`) No\n- New/changed network calls? (`Yes/No`) No\n- Command/tool execution surface changed? (`Yes/No`) No\n- Data access scope changed? (`Yes/No`) No\n- If any `Yes`, explain risk + mitigation:\n\n## Repro + Verification\n\n### Environment\n\n- OS: Linux\n- Runtime/container: local Node.js checkout\n- Model/provider: n/a (gateway-side reply recombination)\n- Integration/channel (if any): reproduced against the gateway non-streaming `chat.send` path; user report was on Matrix\n- Relevant config (redacted): n/a\n\n### Steps\n\n1. Produce a non-streaming assistant reply whose formatted block is emitted across multiple final payloads.\n2. Include indentation-sensitive content such as nested YAML, a nested list, or a fenced code block.\n3. Observe the stored/broadcast final message text.\n\n### Expected\n\n- Indentation from each payload chunk is preserved in the final combined reply.\n\n### Actual\n\n- Leading whitespace at payload boundaries was trimmed away, flattening structured content.\n\n## Evidence\n\nAttach at least one:\n\n- [ ] Failing test/log before + passing after\n- [ ] Trace/log snippets\n- [x] Screenshot/recording\n- [ ] Perf numbers (if relevant)\n\nAdded focused regression coverage for:\n- the authored single-newline separator case\n- an indentation-sensitive `/btw` YAML side result\n- `CRLF` boundary trimming\n\nThe linked user issue includes before/after screenshots of the real-world symptom.\n\n## Human Verification (required)\n\nWhat you personally verified (not just CI), and how:\n\n- Verified scenarios: targeted gateway regression test for the single-newline recombination edge case; targeted `/btw` side-result regression test for an indented YAML block; targeted `CRLF` boundary regression coverage; targeted lint on the changed files; repo pre-commit checks during commit.\n- Edge cases checked: whitespace-only payload chunks are still ignored; separator insertion still only happens when adjacent chunks are not already separated by line breaks; authored single-newline separators are preserved instead of expanded to blank lines; `CRLF` boundaries do not leave stray carriage returns.\n- What you did **not** verify: live Matrix delivery against a running instance, broader streaming reply behavior outside the existing `/btw` block-side-result coverage, or full-repo test suites.\n\n## Review Conversations\n\n- [x] I replied to or resolved every bot review conversation I addressed in this PR.\n- [x] I left unresolved only the conversations that still need reviewer or maintainer judgment.\n\nIf a bot review conversation is addressed by this PR, resolve that conversation yourself. Do not leave bot review conversation cleanup for maintainers.\n\n## Compatibility / Migration\n\n- Backward compatible? (`Yes/No`) Yes\n- Config/env changes? (`Yes/No`) No\n- Migration needed? (`Yes/No`) No\n- If yes, exact upgrade steps:\n\n## Failure Recovery (if this breaks)\n\n- How to disable/revert this change quickly: revert commits `6b2461a11`, `c753cd0af`, and `d667f18f1` (or revert the PR branch changes as a unit)\n- Files/config to restore: `src/gateway/server-methods/chat.ts`, `src/gateway/server-methods/server-methods.test.ts`, and `src/gateway/server.chat.gateway-server-chat.test.ts`\n- Known bad symptoms reviewers should watch for: unexpected extra blank lines between merged payload chunks, unexpected loss of an authored single newline between chunks, stray carriage returns from `CRLF` boundaries, or lost indentation in `/btw` side results\n\n## Risks and Mitigations\n\n- Risk: preserving authored separators changes the old trim/join behavior for payloads that already end in a single newline.\n  - Mitigation: this is intentional, explicitly regression-tested, and still bounded by the same whitespace-only-chunk skipping plus separator insertion only when neither side already provides a line break.\n- Risk: preserving chunk text could expose `CRLF` edge cases at outer boundaries.\n  - Mitigation: the combiner now trims `CRLF` / `CR` / `LF` consistently at the start/end, with targeted regression coverage.\n- Risk: reviewers may mistake this PR for a duplicate of #55960.\n  - Mitigation: this description now names the exact layer split: `#55960` fixes directive parsing, this PR fixes gateway non-streaming recombination.\n",
